The paper focuses on instance segmentation in 3D biomedical images using deep learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach also involves utilizing weak annotation and developing a novel two-stage model, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of insufficient training data and annotation difficulties, which are common issues in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) related to image analysis.
